# 1. Ignore everything by default
*

# 2. Allow all directories (so Git can find the files inside them)
!*/

# 3. Explicitly allow your source and project files
!*.v
!*.sv
!*.py
!*.do
!*.md
!.gitignore

# 4. Optional: If you want to keep specific folders like 'Labs' or 'Projects'
# even if they are empty, Git still needs a file inside them.